    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-03-30T13:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-03-30T13:00:00-05:00" n="94"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d94">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">865.85/258a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Minister in Costa Rica</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hornibrook</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-03-30T13:00:00-05:00"
                            >March 30, 1941—1 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>45. Department’s 43, March 28, 2 p.m. and your 51, March 29, 10 a.m.<note n="7"
                        xml:id="d94fn7">Latter not printed.</note> Please at once seek an interview
                    with the President and give him the information contained in the following
                    circular telegram which is being sent to all our chiefs of mission in the other
                    American Republics:</p>
                <p>[Here follows text of circular telegram of March 30, printed in <ref
                        target="frus1941v06#pg_185">volume VI, page 185</ref>.]</p>
                <p>In view of these circumstances, the suggestion contained in the final sentence of
                    the Department’s No. 43 of March 28, 2 p.m., is no longer pertinent. The
                    Department will be interested in learning of <pb facs="0094" n="86"
                        xml:id="pg_86"/> the decision of the Costa Rican Government regarding the
                    two vessels at Puntarenas. The situation which has developed in the United
                    States illustrates the desirability of maximum precautionary measures.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Welles</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
